caption: Table 1: Parameters used for figure fig. 2b
description: This table lists the hyperparameters used to generate Figure 2b of the paper.  The figure shows the trajectory of model parameters in a 2D space under different learning algorithms. The hyperparameters control aspects of the learning process, including the number of iterations, sample size, scaling factor, and regularization parameter.

caption: Table 2: Parameters used for figure fig. 2c
description: This table lists the hyperparameters used for the experiment in Figure 2c of the paper.  The parameters control aspects of the simulation, including the number of iterations, sample size, initial scale, transition probability matrix, mean of class 0, average number of iterations, step size, and regularization parameter.

caption: Table 3: Parameters used for fig. 2f
description: This table lists the hyperparameters used for the experiment shown in Figure 2f of the paper.  It includes the number of iterations, sample size, number of runs, step size, and regularization parameter used in the logistic regression model for the Housing dataset.
